ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Even if one's own research area doesn't intersect too much with this subject matter, this is a good course to take: to learn associators, multiple zeta values, knot invariant, etc.
A collection of topics organized around the common theme of the pentagon equation and its variations, that appear across several fields in math.
It is a very interesting course and fundamental to many areas of mathematics. Sooner or later everyone will need this knowledge.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It deepened my knowledge of my discipline, because I got to know some things about what was dealt with in the paper I presented. Maybe I'll be using some stuffs that I learned in this class in my research.
The course barely let me scratch the surface of the many topics it covered, many of which were interesting but that were presented without any depth.
